      "id": "GENUS_RIPARIA",
      "name": "Riparia",
      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "Sand martins — the smallest and brownest of Sweden's swallows, colonial nesters in sandy riverbanks, sand quarries, and sea cliffs. Each pair excavates a tunnel 30–90 cm deep in bare sand, ending in a nesting chamber — a feat of engineering for a bird weighing just 13 grams. Sand martin colonies can number thousands of pairs and create dramatic, buzzing spectacles when the birds return to their colony after feeding. They are among the earliest summer migrants to arrive in Sweden in spring, and their presence at a colony site can be assessed instantly by the dark rings of nest holes peppering the sand face.",
